# A light [[food]], such as an [[appetizer]], that is served before a meal.
# (''by extension''): Anything of [[secondary]] concern; not the primary one.

====Quotations====
*'''1920''' — [[w:G. K. Chesterton|G. K. Chesterton]], ''[[s:The New Jerusalem|The New Jerusalem]]'', Ch. XIII
*:It seems quaintest of all when, at some Jewish luncheon parties, a tray of hats is actually handed round, and each guest helps himself to a hat as a sort of '''''hors d'oeuvre'''''.
*'''1925''' — [[w:F. Scott Fitzgerald|F. Scott Fitzgerald]], ''[[s:The Great Gatsby|The Great Gatsby]]'', Ch. 3
*: On buffet tables, garnished with glistening '''hors-d’oeuvre''', spiced baked hams crowded against salads of harlequin designs and pastry pigs and turkeys bewitched to a dark gold.

